inn1.comm: What a cracking ball first up from Sharif! This is full and bending away outside off. Gayle has a loose waft at it and sends a thin edge to the keeper. Sharif sends Gayle back for a first-ball duck. Dream start for him and Scotland
nice, tight delivery outside the off stump, he lets it go
shapes it away a little bit from outside off, looked like he wanted to defend but lets it go again
shapes it away again from Hope, nice seam position of the ball to swing it away after pitching it on good length. Left alone again
much closer and fuller on the off stump, Hope defends it back with the full face of the bat
pulls the length back just a tad and Hope pushes it back towards mid-off with hard hands
fuller and Wheal explores the channel, Lewis doesn't
back of a length and angling across off, no shot again
full and just a shade outside off, defensively pushed into the covers of the front foot
really full on middle and leg, Lewis stretches out and drives between midwicket and mid-on
back of a length and angling away outside off, Lewis gets right behind the line in defence
similar length and slanting away outside off, Lewis does not go after it again

Sharif sends Hope back for a duck too. Nice and full, perfectly pitched delivery, angling in, then cunningly straightening away outside off. Hope is opened up. He simply hangs his bat out and nicks it behind to Cross. WI: 2 for 2
Sharif hits an in-between length outside off, Samuels leaves it be
a bit fuller and much closer to off stump, bends away, Samuels pokes and is beaten on the outside edge
full and largely holds its line outside off, ignored
back of a length and in the channel outside off, no shot
really full and angling in at off stump, catches Samuels on the crease. He hastily jabs his bat down and squirts an inside edge behind square leg to get off the mark
Wheal puts it on a length on off, finds extra gloves and raps the glove even as Samuels softens his grip. Short leg in business
much fuller and swinging in at off, Samuels leading-edges the ball to cover
back of a length and rises on off, Samuels rises with it and pats it down
short and shoved down leg, no shot. Re-set the radar, Wheal
on a length outside off, jumps from there, Samuels yanks his bottom hand off the bat and runs it to backward point
lifter outside off, ignored
back of a length and outside off, Samuels rides the bounce and glides it down to third man
full on middle, Samuels plays back to it and nurdles the ball in front of midwicket
full and angling away outside off, Lewis presses forward, meets the pitch of the ball and pushes a single to mid-on
really full and angling in, Samuels, however, camps back in the crease and fetches a single to square leg
overpitched and outside off, nailed through the covers. Lewis stretches out, meets the pitch again, and drills a cover drive. Fetch that
full and tight, angling away outside off, Lewis watches it through to the keeper

full and swinging in against the angle, Lewis eyes up a big drive again, this time he sends an inside edge onto the unprotected right knee. Sharif is swinging it in and out. Lewis cops a blow on the inside of the knee. He needs some medical attention
back of a length and nipping down leg for a wide. Cross throws himself to his left to stop the ball
good length and sliding into off stump with the angle, Samuels is happy to hang back in the crease and defend it
good length, swinging in at off, Samuels inside-edges it beside his feet on the leg side
on a length, angling in at off, Wheal finds extra bounce. Samuels yanks his bottom hand off the bat and pats it down
short and slanting in at the top of off stump, Samuels' back-foot defence intervenes
full and angling into a forward-defensive push back to the bowler
nice and full, angling in from wide of the crease, Wheal catches Samuels playing around his front pad and missing. But this was heading down with the sharp angle from over the wicket
pitches outside off, swings and hits the front pad as Lewis falls over the flick
full and angling across off, Lewis shows restraint and shoulders arms
good length and shifts his line wide of off, Lewis shoulders arms again
on a length and outside off, Lewis drives on the up but finds backward point
half-tracker outside off, begs on its knees to be hit. Lewis obliges. He rises on top of the bounce and forces the ball between extra cover and mid-off
full on leg stump, defended to mid-off
short, arrowed in at the top of off. Samuels gets on top of it and blocks it back down the pitch
full and angling into leg stump, Samuels doesn't get enough bat on the glance, deflected away to leg gully
back of a length and holds its line outside off, defensively dropped into the covers
bouncer on off, 135ks, Samuels rocks his head out of the way. The ball sails over him to the keeper. That's too high - wide
in-between length outside off - neither drivable nor pullable - hastily jabbed away off the back foot to backward point
Wheal ventures another bouncer outside off, too high again, second wide of the over

Samuels gets going with an aerial punch that bursts through the hands of Sole at cover-point. Back of a length and outside off, Samuels leaps off his feet and forces it in the air. Sole is a touch late to dive to his left and misses the (half)chance
back of a length, skidding off the pitch to beat the pull and hit Samuels high on the thigh
short and in the channel, left alone
Lewis rises on top of a short ball outside off and punches to cover-point
pitched up and outside off, driven through the line to mid-off. Coetzer effects a direct hit at the non-striker's end and they steal a single via a ricochet
short and outside off, Samuels rolls his wrists and controls a pull to deep midwicket
full and angling in, catches Samuels on the crease, pins him on the pad but this is going down leg again
short, wide, instead of carting it out of the park Samuels simply slashes to backward point
full and attached with width, scythed straight to cover-point
back of a length and zipping away outside off past the outside edge
much fuller and angling across off, Lewis presses forward and lets it go
back of a length and angling away outside off, Lewis continues to show patience. Left alone again
full and angling across off, barely 130ks, Lewis throws his bat at the ball and slices a thick outside edge that flies to deep third man
Sharif puts it on an in-between length on off stump, Samuels stays leg-side of the ball and belts it straight back to Sharif
skidding into the pads from around the wicket, defensively dabbed to the leg side
shortish and speared down the leg side for a wide
tossed up liberally outside off, drilled to the covers
a bit too full for the sweep, Lewis misses it, the ball slides down leg for a wide
full on middle, forward and driven to the covers again
jabbed back to the bowler
very full on off stump, pushed firmly to long-off
wide of the crease, holds its line outside off, Samuels has a big whoosh... and only collects fresh air
full and probing away in the channel, Lewis ignores it. He has shown great patience today
good length and skidding into the leg stump, inside-edged through midwicket
yorker tailing down leg, Samuels fall over and is hit on the front pad just above the boot
another very full ball slanting down leg, beats the big flick of Samuels. The batsman is caught on the crease again
length ball on off, stabbed back to the bowler
on a length and outside off, Samuels stays leg-side of the ball and hacks it to mid-off
Lewis ventures down the track and belts a full ball back to Sole
spinning down leg, beats the sweep, wide called
tossed outside off and breaks away, scoops a drive in the air and over cover
too full and outside off, Samuels flays it away to the off-side sweeper
full and outside off, leans into the drive and hits the ball to the covers
shorter and outside off, Lewis goes back and punches it back to Sole
sliding in on middle and leg, Lewis thrusts his bat in front of the pad in defence
full on the stumps, defended back
bouncer outside off, trampolines off the pitch, beats Samuels' hook and the leaping keeper. Five wides
bouncer on middle, well directed, ducks under it
short on off, jabbed to mid-off
on a length and outside off, Samuels throws his hands at the ball, loses his shape, and inside-edges it to mid-on
short and wide outside off, Samuels goes after it and smears it up and over the covers
very full and angling in on middle, Samuels plays back and blocks it to the leg side
very full at leg stump, jammed down to long-on
tossed outside off, driven through the line to the right of sweeper cover
dropped short and wide outside off, Samuels swings hard, so hard that he loses his shape. The keeper whips the bails off but Samuels' back leg went nowhere
full and outside off, carves it to the left of sweeper cover
full and angling across off from round the wicket, dead-batted into the covers
full and sliding away just outside off, Samuels presses forward and defends to the off side
tight line on off, blocked to cover off the front foot
hip-high short ball just a shade outside off, Lewis pummels a pull to the midwicket boundary. It sat up and Lewis gave it a proper humpty
short and angling away outside off, Lewis arches his back and lets it go

Wheal runs to his right from deep square leg, stretches out his right hand as far as he could, but the ball evades him and sails into the boundary. Evans puts more effort into this short ball outside off and forces the batsman to miscue a pull
Wheal overcorrects - half-volley outside off - and is sent over the straight boundary. He gets underneath the length and pumps it over the bowler's head
Lewis gets behind this back-of-a-length ball on off, and defends it back down the pitch
full outside off, and crunched past cover's right. Goes to Sharif at long off, who chases to his left and intercepts
good length just outside off, no spin and left alone by Lewis
full just outside off stump, one step forward and driven to long off for a walking single
full on middle stump, big stride forward and turned off his pads to square leg
good length on middle, worked towards the off side

full on middle stump and Samuels smacks this down the ground but man down. It's hit Lewis! And he's on the floor. Lewis turned to get out of the ball's way, but the shot thumped his left thigh. He's squealing on the floor, but his team-mates - in the dugout - are having a giggle. The physio's finally done with his magic (spray, and other stuff)
good length outside off, rocks backwards, and cuts to deep backward point
full outside off, and Samuels frees his arms. Drives through to deep extra for a comfortable single
full on middle stump, squares Lewis up, but manages to drive - inside out - to mid off
full outside off again, takes a step towards the off side and crunches a drive to mid off
full on leg stump, down on one knee, but misses the sweep. The ball trickles down to short fine leg, and Leask's lbw appeal is turned down. Would've gone down leg for certain
good length outside off, but spinning inwards this time. Samuels goes onto the back foot and punches to long off
full just outside off, takes a step towards the off side and drives to cover
full again, but wider outside off. Slaps this drive to cover once again. Width was there get under this ball
full just outside off, caresses this down the ground. Straight to long off
good length, but wide outside off. Mistimes his cut, and the ball trickles down to point
good length outside off, but straightens after pitching. Punched off the back foot past cover to the man in the deep

past first slip! This got the edge but past the keeper's right. Full on middle stump, and but ball was angling across Samuels. Tried the on-drive and took a feather off his bat, but alas. Races away past short third man thereafter
full on off stump, tapped back to the bowler off the front foot
full on leg stump, skips forward and smothers this to long on
good length outside off, turns into Samuels' pads. Flicked towards square leg
low full toss on leg stump, misses the yorker but doesn't get punished for it. Driven to long on
full on leg stump, and well swept. Was quick to get down this time, and slapped past the square-leg umpire
wide outside off, and on a good length. Lewis tries to cut it square, but bottom edged
full on middle and leg, takes a charge down the ground, but check-drives to mid on
full on off stump, Samuels gets his front leg towards the off side and misses the defense. The ball hits his pad
full on off stump, runs down the wicket and defends back to the bowler
good length outside leg stump, misses the flick, but the ball hits his thigh. Runs away to short fine leg
full outside leg, and swept once again! Lewis displays his strength behind square on the leg side once again. Smart shot with fine leg inside the circle
full and wide outside off, drives away from his body but stopped at cover
tossed up this time, but too wide outside off. Crunches this drive to deep extra cover with relative ease
good length just outside off, Lewis sees this ball through to him, and punches with the bat's open face. To cover point, and shows his disappointment after missing out

misfield at short third man! Allows them to take two extra runs. Good length outside off, and punched off the back foot, took the outside edge so the ball went behind square. The ball goes between the fielders legs there
full on middle stump, tapped towards the leg side
full just outside off, defended back to Leask
it's hit the keeper's knee! And he's down now. Overpitched outside off, and Lewis misses the drive. Pings Cross hard but he's fine now. Wobbles across to the other side for the next over
full on off stump and angling into his pads, driven towards mid on off the front foot
back of a length outside off, tries to slap this square, but can't connect. The ball stays low too, and goes under his bat
full on off stump, and driven to cover. Samuels is scampering across for the single, but direct hit at the non-striker's! Dragged his bat in before the stumps were broken
that's his third fifty! Full outside off, and crunches this drive to the deep extra cover boundary. A terrific shot to get to the milestone
back of a length on middle stump, forces Lewis to go back, and defend off the back foot
full just outside off, pings this drive down the ground to the man at long off
half tracker outside off, turns away from Lewis, but mistimes the drive to cover
full just outside off, punched off the back foot to cover
good length outside off stump, punched off the back foot. But straight to the fielder at cover. Once again too many dots from Samuels. That's his 49th dot
full and wide outside off, and smacks this drive past cover. There's the man in the deep, though
full on leg, and swept behind square. To the man at square leg this time. A good fielding position for Lewis at all times
good length outside off, but near the tram-lines. Lewis shoulders his arms and looks surprised that it wasn't called a wide
good length just outside off, Samuels shuffles across to the off side and turns it off his pads to deep midwicket
good length just outside off, Lewis covers his off stump and taps this to cover
low full toss wide outside off, smacks it to long off but off the bat's toe end. They walk across for the single

slower ball, full on off stump. Attempts the straight drive but the bat turns in his hand as he's through his shot too early. Tapped to cover but they're off for the quick single. Rocket throw at the batsman's end, but misses the direct hit
full on off stump, and that's the cutter once again. Lewis opens his bat's face and runs this down to third man. That's the hundred partnership as well
full just outside off, smacked to long off

good length outside off and zips straight through to the keeper. Samuels misses the defense and the keeper takes the bails off. They're appealing for the stumping. Has Samuels' back leg dragged out? Well, yes, for a bit, but he brought it in just in time. Sharp work from Cross though
full just outside off, defended off the front foot
full just outside off, walks down the wicket. Tapped to the bowler
full just outside off, smacked past the bowler's right to long on

full on middle stump, but turns away after pitching. Lewis tries to sweep but misses completely. The ball hits his front pad, right in front of middle stump, but the appeal's turned down by the umpire. Looked mighty close there
full on off stump, and driven down the ground to long off
good length on off stump, punched off the back foot and sent back to the bowler
good length just outside off, punched with the bat's open face past point
good length outside off, and tapped off the back foot. Sent back to Evans
goes for the big one! Full outside off, and tries to lift this over cover. It's the offcutter, so takes the thick outside edge. Falls between point and the man in the deep
good length just outside off, Samuels walks towards the off side and fends it back to Evans
full outside off, drives this with the square bat. Through to the man in the deep for a walking single
full just outside off, pings this down the ground to long off. Samuels doing a better job at rotating the strike now
good length on middle but extra bounce! Lewis does well to nudge this off his pads to square leg
full toss on middle stump, and Samuels muscles this down the ground. Hits Leask's right hand, and Lewis is lucky that the ball didn't roll onto the stumps
full on middle stump, defended towards the on side
good length outside off, punched off the back foot with the square bat. Straight to cover point
good length outside off, slaps this off the back foot to mid off. Frustrated on missing out, Lewis
an attempted yorker that's eventually a full toss. Muscled to mid on off the front foot
good length outside off, tries to chop it down fine past the keeper. Manages to poke it to short third man
full on off stump, drives with the ball angling towards his pads, but only to mid on
it's the cutter outside off stump. Samuels waits for it patiently and runs it fine to third man
good length outside off. Tapped to cover for a quick run, and Lewis manages to scamper across without much danger
full outside off, an expansive drive from Samuels with a high back lift. Runs it to long off
starts off with the offcutter, defended off the front foot to Berrington. Sees the first ball carefully, Samuels
fuller on off stump, Samuels is through his drive too early and takes the outside edge. Trickles down to point, and allows the batsmen to rotate strike
close! Good length outside off, and Lewis tried to run that fine for a boundary. Just past his bat's outside edge. High risk shot for a high reward, but doesn't come off this time
good length outside off again, punched away from his body and sent to deep extra cover
full on off stump, tapped to the leg side with soft hands. Samuels calls early for the single
full outside off, cut off the back foot, but straight to point
back of a length outside off, flat-bats this past the bowler's left. The big heave only fetches him one since long off's positioned there
inside edge, but runs down to fine leg! Good length outside off, and Lewis attempted the pull. Inches away from his leg stump, though. West Indies making their intention clear

full on off stump, and Lewis tries a big leg-side heave. Doesn't come off again, and hits his back leg. Impact on middle and off, and the umpire has no hesitations. Lewis has to go, and the partnership is finally broken
short outside off, but way too slow. Pokes at it from near his chest to point and he's off the mark
overpitched just outside off, and Samuels' drive doesn't come off. Toe-ends it to cover
full just outside off, caresses the drive to cover, but MacLeod is quick to pounce onto it. No run
full on off stump, comfortably tapped past the non-striker's right to long on
slower ball, very full outside off. Forced to reach at it, and toe-ends a drive to deep extra cover
full on leg stump, and Samuels flicks this fine but looks like it comes off his pad! Either way it's way past the keeper's left, and his dive isn't good enough. Moves on to 49
full just outside off, and driven to mid off. No single
full on off stump, through his drive early and takes the inside edge. The ball flies away towards midwicket
full just outside off, and driven away from his body. Drops just short of cover! Close.
full just outside off, attempts to drive, but off the bat's outside. Goes square to point
good length just outside off, punched off the back foot to Wheal
good length outside off, but angling into Hetmyer. Cuts this from near his body, and plays it finer than he wanted. Runs down to third man
full just outside off, tapped to the off side and he scampers across for the run! His 30th fifty
full and wide outside off, tapped to cover point but the fielder has a shy at the stumps. Direct hit at the non-striker's but Samuels was always in
good length just outside off, punched once again off the back foot. This time to mid on. And drinks once again.
tossed up outside off, spins slightly inwards. Driven straight past the bowler's left to long off
one slip in place now. On a good length outside off, and Hetmyer goes onto the back foot. Punched to cover
full on middle and leg, big heave towards the leg side from Hetmyer. Whipped off his boots to deep backward square

taken at wide long off! Full outside off, and Samuels looks to accelerate. Tries to drive this over cover, but he's sliced this shot. Sole races across to his left and slides along the ground to complete a sharp catch

out next ball! It's the drifter outside off, and the ball zips straight through. He tries to defend off the front foot - rather tentatively, may I add - and the ball takes the faint outside edge. On a hat-trick!
full outside off stump, Tries to defend and off the edge! Wide of first slip, though and Powell survives
skids on outside off, darts past the outside edge
very full and outside off, driven down to long-off
speared on a length on off, hangs back and pushes to short midwicket
back of a length on middle, forced down to long-on off the back foot
shortish and outside off, Holder reaches out for the ball with his hands and slaps the ball away to sweeper cover
picked off the pads through backward square leg
tossed up and breaks in on off, Holder defends it back to him
looped up outside off, Holder chips it right over the bowler's head
punched with the turn to long-on off the back foot
skids on off, forced to cover off the back foot
darted on middle, shuffles across and punches to short midwicket
quicker and turns in on off, jabbed away to the leg side off the back foot
very full and slanting in at off stump, flicked away but can't get it past short midwicket
clipped off the hips to the left of short fine leg
too full and outside off, driven through the covers
back of a length on middle stump, worked with the wrists to deep midwicket
back of a length on off, cramps the batsman for room, and forces him to punch down to long-on
tight line on off, defended off the front foot
shorter and outside off, keeps low, cracked to sweeper cover off the back foot
worked with the spin to square leg
might full on off, dug out to short midwicket
tossed up on off, turns, dips, inside-edged to the leg side
Powell stays beside the line and dabs a single square on the off side
back of a length on off, swatted down to long-on off the back foot
pitched up and outside off, speared to sweeper cover, where there's a misfield, allowing another run
sliced off the outside half behind point
back of a length and angling into a leg-side punch to the right of midwicket
full on off, tapped to mid-off
full and wide, carved to sweeper cover
full and angling into a front-foot punch to short midwicket's left
back of a length and outside off, lets the ball slide off the face behind point
Powell rides the bounce of this short ball outside off and secures a single to third man

Holder has been bounced out, and West Indies are six down. Dug in short on off, skids off the pitch, and rushes Holder into a hook. He is late onto it and sends a top edge fluttering to short midwicket moving to his left
full-toss on off, jabbed back to the bowler
pitched up and outside off, Brathwaite strides forward and drives smoothly to cover
good length and angling in on middle, Brathwaite plays around his front pad and defends it
short and angling into a back-foot punch to long-on
floated full and outside off, driven fluently to mid-off off the front foot
tip and run to the left of backward point
length ball on off, presses forward and hits it to mid-off
back of a length and outside off, dabbed to short cover
punched through the line to long-off for a jogged single
flatter and breaks in, forced to short midwicket
on a length and outside off, glides it behind point
full and spins in, leading-edges it back to the bowler
back of a length and straightens his line, turned to midwicket

That's outta here! Brathwaite has muscled it. New balls, please. This was tossed up invitingly outside off. The length is too full. Brathwaite gets underneath the length and golf-swings it out of the park
shorter on the hips, goes back and clips it square of short fine leg
back of a length and angling down leg for a wide
back of a length and angling in on middle, Brathwaite inches forward and defends it back
fullish and outside off eased down to long-off
punched down to long-off
run away to backward point
pitched up on off stump, thumped down the ground
back of a length on off, Brathwaite leans back and chops it to backward point
wide yorker, squeezed to backward point
chopped behind again, this time to the right of the keeper
floated full and outside off, laced to long-off

Sharif sends the leg stump cartwheeling. What a sight for a fast bowler. In-between length from Sharif, angling into Powell, this length is nether driveable nor pullable. The batsman jabs at it and inside-edges it onto the leg stump, which has been knocked out
full and nipping in, forced to midwicket off the inside half
back of a length and outside off, keeps low, squeezed to third man
Brathwaite rides the bounce of this short ball outside off and dabs to third man
full outside off, plays down the wrong line and is beaten
slower ball, full on off, driven down to long-off
tip and run to cover
back of a length and outside off, shovel-pulls it along the ground to deep midwicket
full and outside off, chipped in front of long-on
back of a length and outside off, lets it slide off the face to backward point
wide of the crease, holds its line outside off, finds the outside edge but does not carry to the diving wicketkeeper

Berrington ventures wide of the crease again, this time he sends down a slower short ball outside off. Nurse throws his bat at the ball and only carves outside edge straight into the lap of short third man
full and just a shade outside off, jammed out
too straight in line, turned to the leg side
nasty short ball, fizzes off the pitch and raps the glove as Paul rises with it and takes his eyes off the ball
slower cutter outside off, dabs to Berrington at backward point and sets off. The fielder misses the direct hit. The batsman undoes his steps and reaches safety
full and angling in at off, straightens slightly, takes the outside edge and rolls to backward point
on a length and outside off, takes the outside edge and runs away to the third man boundary
good length on off, played back to the bowler
chips a leading edge to backward point
full on middle and leg, tapped down to wide long-on
wide yorker, beats Brathwaite
shuffles across and whips from off stump to deep midwicket
full-toss just outside off, squeezed to backward point
shuffles across and tickles it off the pads to square leg
low full-toss on off, bunted to cover and Brathwaite retains strike
back of a length and outside off, worked through midwicket. They chance a two and get it

Excellent overhead catch from Munsey at backward point. Credit to Wheal too. He sends down a slower offcutter wide outside off, Brathwaite shuffles across and aims to clip it over midwicket. Instead, he plays early and chips a leading edge to backward point
full and angling in, falls over the flick and is hit on the pad but this seems to be heading down leg
The middle stump is floored. Wheal wraps up West Indies' innings with a very full ball - a near yorker - the batsman plays all around it and loses his middle stump

inn2.comm: wide of the crease, skidding into the thigh off the pitch. Cross is beaten for pace and is pinged on the thigh but that's too high
wide of the crease again, full and holds its line outside off, presses forward and drives to mid-off
full and angling into the pads, flicked firmly but straight to midwicket
full and holds its line outside off, left alone
yorker, nips in on middle, dug back to Roach
full and darted outside off, ignored. Maiden first up from Roach
back of a length and outside off, serenely punched to cover
shortish and angling in on middle, defended off the back foot
inswinger, takes the inside edge and rolls to deep square leg as Scotland open their account
back of a length and slanted down leg for a wide
back of a length and shapes back in, the batsman is pinned to the crease and squirts an inside edge onto the thigh pad
length ball on off, gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler
punched up to mid-off
full and outside off, punched between covers and mid-off
short and attached with plenty of width outside off. Coetzer slashes with all his might but can't keep it down. He holes out to Lewis at backward point. He jumps and pouches the ball safely
full and outside off, 137ks, left alone
wide of the crease, zipping through the channel, left alone
fuller on off, pushed to covers off the front foot
back of a length and outside off, Jones gets on top of the bounce and stylishly punches in the gap at the covers. What a shot to get off the mark
rides the bounce of this short one outside off and glides to third man
Jones shuffles across off and skies a pull. Roach does not attack the ball. He hangs back and lets the ball drop in front of him at long leg
back of a length outside off, guided to backward point

Holder uproots the off stump and lets out a big roar. West Indies are fired up. Holder goes wide of the crease, angles it into Cross and finds extra bounce to boot. Cross is cramped up, he hops, and gloves it onto the stumps
bouncer on middle, ducks under it. Wide called because of height
good length and outside off, the batsman lets it go
tapped to backward point
full and outside off, defended into the covers off the front foot
full and outside off, angled down to third man
full on the stumps, squeezed behind square leg
back of a length and outside off, guided off the face to point
full on middle, bunted back down the pitch
punched to cover, the ball bursts through the hands of Samuels. He did save a boundary
full and outside off, played up to the covers, Samuels tumbles to his right and half(stops) the ball
good length and angling into a push to mid-on
tucked off the hips to fine leg
worked away to the right of square leg
worked away to the same region
shuffles across and skies a pull wide of square leg
Roach has bounced out Jones. This is a chest-hunting short ball on middle stump, Jones shuffles across and pulls it in the air. He finds Rovman Powell at long leg
short and outside off, left alone
full and swerving in, takes the inside edge and rolls to the leg side
full and angling in, blocked off the front foot
nudged to fine leg for one
bouncer outside off, left alone
short and slanting in on middle, McLeod hops and fends it down
short and kicks up on off, fended off again
gets on top of a short ball outside off and punches between cover and mid-off
chipped in the air but between midwicket and square leg
back of a length and outside off, punched to mid-off
bouncer on middle, ducks under it
full and sliding into the pads, glanced away fine for four
full on middle, defended back
back of a length on off, punched to cover
back of a length and around off, dabbed to backward point
full and speared in on middle, Berrington covers up in defence
full on middle, poked to the left of the bowler
back of a length and angling in, punched to mid-on
full on middle, played to mid-on
back of a length on off, tapped to mid-off
shortish and outside off, punched to cover
short ball, ducks out of the way
full and outside off, driven through the covers
very full on middle, driven to the right of mid-off
short and hits the bat hard as opposed to bat hitting ball
full on middle, shows the full face of the bat and punches smoothly to mid-on
short and outside off, cramps the batsman for room, chopped to backward point
jabbed to cover-point
back of a length on top of off, punched back to the bowler
back of a length and angling into the body, blocked to midwicket
back of a length on off, gets behind the line and blocks
punched on the up to backward point
Brathwaite finds the outside edge but it dies in front of Gayle at first slip
full and angling into a front-foot defensive push
full on middle, defended to mid-on. Brathwaite starts with a maiden
leg-stump half-volley, flicked away only as far as long leg
short and hits the pitch hard, flapped away to midwicket
short on middle, defended square on the off side
full on middle, forced to mid-on for a sharp single
back of a length on off, stroked to mid-on
bouncer on middle, ducks under it
good length and outside off, he wafts and only collects fresh air
overpitched and outside off, leans into it and caresses a drive through the covers. So easy on the eye...
back of a length on off, played up to mid-off
good length on middle, shuffles across off and turns to midwicket
clipped off the hips to square leg
full on the stumps, tapped to mid-on for a risky single. Roach takes his eyes off the ball and misfields
short and shoved down leg, beats the pull, just loops past the glove. Leg-side wide it is
full on middle, blocked back to the bowler
back of a length and outside off, stabbed to cover
bouncer on middle, ducks under it
shorter and outside off, ducks under again
another leg-side wide
good length on middle, presses forward and pushes to mid-on
full and attacking the stumps, defended to mid-on again
full just outside off, tapped to mid off off the front foot
back of a length outside off, MacLeod gets on top of this ball, and crunches a cut past cover. Finds the gap between the two infielders and Samuels' lazy footwork in the deep ensures it's four more
short outside off stump, soars over MacLeod's shoulders and through to the keeper
full on middle and leg, driven to the on side this time. Only to mid on
good length on middle stump, shuffles across to the off side and flicks to square leg
good length on off stump, covers his off stump and punches it off his back foot to mid on. That's the over, and drinks too.
ful on off stump, shuffles across to the off side and bunts it to mid on
short, and pulled square! Not too high for Berrington to deal with, and he got into position early. Caresses this past square leg
good length outside off, opens his stance and punches it to cover for a quick single
full on middle stump, leans into the drive and taps it to mid on
back of a length slower ball on middle stump. MacLeod has to wait ages for it, before turning it off his pads to square leg

short ball on middle stump. The batsman's in two minds and he doesn't duck in time. The ball goes just over his shoulder and down the leg side. Appeal for caught behind (one would assume), but the umpire laughs it off

What's going on here? Nurse has appealed. The umpires are consulting. Soft signal not out from umpire Wilson. Full outside off, and the bunt has ricocheted onto his boots and through to Nurse. But, the ball had bounced into the pitch before hitting the shoe.
full just outside off again, defended back to Nurse
flighted outside off, driven past the non-striker to the man at long on
back of a length outside off, rocks back and punches off the back foot to Nurse
full just outside off, big stride forward and defended
full outside off stump, driven away from his body to long off. Just two off the over
good length just outside off, uses the depth of his crease to chip this over the bowler. Punched, from near the bat's toe end
back of a length outside off, slower ball this time. And fended off the back foot
back of a length outside off, nudged off his waist to square leg for a quick single
back of a length outside off this time, blocked off the back foot. Played to cover
short and sharp! On middle, and forces the batsman to drop his knees. Does well to get out of the ball's way
full on off stump, covers his off stump by shuffling towards that direction before driving to mid on
flat on middle stump, Berrington rocks back and taps this past the non-striker's left to long on
overpitched outside off, punches off the back foot to short mid off
well stopped by Nurse! Full outside off, and crunched straight down. The bowler dives to his left and intercepts
full on the fourth-stump line, punched off the back foot to long on again. Easy for these two
good length outside off, defended back to Nurse
full just outside off, tapped back to Nurse
back of a length outside off, turned off his pads to backward square
good length on off stump, angling into the batsman, and nudged towards midwicket
appeal for caught behind! But the umpire's quick to say no. Good length on middle stump, and going down the leg side. Tried to flick, but can't connect. Comes off his thigh pad
good length just outside off, angling in once again, and flicked to the leg side
good length outside off, defended off the back foot with soft hands
good length just outside off, and zips straight through. Left alone by the batsman
full outside off stump, tapped down the ground to long off
full just outside off again, turns into MacLeod. Punched off the back foot to long on
full just outside off, turns into the batsman again. Driven away from his body to cover
full just outside off, smothered towards midwicket off the front foot
full on middle stump, uses the depth of the crease to flick towards the leg side
one handed stunner! Full on middle stump, and defended back to the bowler. Off the bat's toe end, so it's in the air. Nurse dives to his left and takes a wonderful catch
back of a length outside off, defended off the back foot to mid off
full outside off stump, defended towards cover off the front foot
pulled over midwicket! Short outside off, and smacked towards the leg side. Misfield by Lewis in the deep
full on off stump, and the defense finds the outside edge! Second slip was there, but no first slip, and the ball goes through that gap
good length outside off, but the ball jags away after pitching. Tries to punch towards cover, but the ball goes past his outside edge
good length outside off, once again left alone by Munsey. No sign of play being stopped at the moment
full on middle and leg, flicked off his pads to midwicket
tossed up full on middle stump, whipped off his pads to fine leg
good length outsie off but angling right in. Defends off the back foot but Nurse appeals for lbw. Did the ball hit the pad first? Naw, off the bat's meat
good length outside off, carved off the back foot to cover with the bat's open face
full on middle stump, driven to Gayle at short mid on
full just outside off, big stride forward and defended back to Nurse
back of a length outside off. Munsey's happy to shoulder his arms
full on off stump, steps forward and drives to cover. Straight to the man there
full and wide outside off. Enticing the batsman to drive, but he doesn't give in. Shoulders his arms once again
full on off stump, big stride forward and defended towards the off side
almost chopped on! Good length outside off, and tries to cut. Too close to his body, and takes the bat's inside edge. Hits his back leg and falls in front of the stumps
full just outside off, carved off the back foot to point. A maiden
full on middle stump, and turning down the leg side. Clipped off his pads to midwicket
full just outside off, defended off the front foot past cover. Brathwaite gives it a chase
full on middle stump, goes deep into the crease and punches towards the non-striker

dropped by Gayle! Good length, quick ball outside off. The batsman tries to defend off the back foot, but takes the outside edge, and hits the keeper's pads. Ricochets towards slip but Gayle's in no position to hold onto it
full just outside off, and Munsey's done hanging around. Down on one knee, and reverse swept over first slip!
full just outside off, drives through the ball, and sends it to cover
crunched! Full outside off, and way too gentle a pace to worry Berrington. Driven extravagantly past cover, and there's nobody in the deep
good length just outside off, gets big on the batsman, but manages to punch towards cover point
good length on off stump, and enough room for Munsey to free his arms. Punches this with the bat's open face. Beats cover, and the chase is futile! Shoulders drooping among the WI fielders
short and wide outside off. Munsey chooses not to chase after it. Left alone
full outside off, drives this well, but cover dives to his left and intercepts this shot. Had four written all over it
short outside off, comfortably cut off the back foot to the man in the deep. Munsey's growing in confidence now
tossed up just outside off. Big stride forward and defended
reverse swept once again! Over short third man this time. Full outside off, and whipped by the batsman. Shouts of catch it, but just over the infielder
full on middle and leg, defended off the front too. Tapped back to Nurse
defended towards the bowler this time

reverse swept once again! Munsey's really taking the charge to Nurse here. Full outside off again, and he's quick to get down on one knee. Not well hit, but enough to lift it over Hetmyer at short third man. This'll hurt West Indies
good length on off stump, and angling further in. Punched off the back foot, but takes the outside edge. Trickles down to deep backward square
good length just outside off, defended off the back foot towards cover
back of a length on off stump, stays on the back foot and fends it back to Roach
good length on leg stump, can't flick it away. Off his pads
good length outside off once more, Munsey shoulders his arms
full outside off, caresses this drive down the ground, but stopped by mid off running to his right
good length just outside off. Cut off the back foot, but intercepted by cover point. Roach returns with a maiden
full just outside off, driven down the ground to long off. Comfortably walk across for the single
dropped by the keeper! Tough chance but we're talking about fine margins now. Good length outside off, and the cut takes the bottom edge. Hits the keeper's gloves and drops
full on leg stump, almost a yorker, and does well to squeeze this back to Nurse
full on middle stump, driven to mid off and they call for the quick single. That's the team hundred
good length outside off, punched off the back foot to deep extra cover. Work for Powell in the deep
overpitched outside off, drives through the ball's line and pings this to cover. Stopped by the fielder there, who dives in front to get his body behind the ball
short on off stump, pulled along the ground this time. Past midwicket, and more runs for Scotland
short on middle stump, but too short reckons the square-leg umpire. Goes down the leg side as well
good length just outside off, but the ball zips off the surface. Extra bounce but well negated by Berrington. Poked towards point
back of a length outside off, tapped with soft hands towards cover
full on off stump, big stride forward and defended towards cover
good length outside off, punched towards cover
full on leg stump, defended towards mid off
good length on leg stump, tries to flick it fine, but can't connect. Off his back leg
good length just outside off, angling in. Defended towards cover

given lbw! Huge wicket. Good length on middle stump, would've gone down the leg side though! Impact was outside leg stump, but oh dear, Berrington's gone. If only this game had DRS. Tried to punch off the back foot towards mid on, but the ball stayed slightly low
good length on middle stump, muscled down the ground to long on
length ball on off stump, but angling into him pads. Turned away towards the leg side
back of a length outside off, punched away from his body to mid off. They scamper across for the single
good length on middle stump, defended in front of his stumps
full on off stump, driven away from his body, but stopped by mid off
good length on middle and leg, forces the batsman to rock back and defend
full just outside off, tries to drive towards the cover but takes the outside edge. Runs down to third man
punched! Good length on off stump, and crunched off the back foot. off the bat's middle and races away to the extra cover boundary. Drinks
tossed up on leg stump, almost a yorker, but manages to squeeze this away to backward square. The first run's completed in flash, and they turn around for the second
full just outside off. Defended towards the off side. Played off the front foot
full on middle stump, prods forward and blocks it towards cover
tossed up on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
good length outside off, stays slightly low, but manages to cut it square. They want the two, but intercepted quickly in the deep this time
full on off stump, driven to Gayle at short mid on. Only three off the over
good length outside off, and the extra bounce finds the bat's outside shoulder. Runs down to third man
good length outside off, punched off the back foot to cover point
top edged over the keeper! Short on off stump, and he attempts an extravagant pull. Manages to get enough off that to send it for four. Despair written all over Holder's face
loopy bouncer on middle stump. Going down leg as the batsman tries to another swipe at it. Doesn't connect this time
short outside off, pulled over midwicket, but doesn't have the timing. In the air, but drops short of deep midwicket
slower ball, full and wide outside off. Driven with soft hands to the man in the deep. Heavy raindrops
good length outside off, cut off the back foot but no real timing behind it. The rain's getting heavy now
good length outside off, angling into Munsey. Carved off the back foot to backward square. And the players are off!
